{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/posts/how-to-create-your-github-profile-readme/","result":{"data":{"logo":null,"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"personalize-your-github-profile-page\" style=\"position:relative;\">Personalize your GitHub profile page<a href=\"#personalize-your-github-profile-page\" aria-label=\"personalize your github profile page permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h1>\n<p>In the past, your ability to customize your GitHub profile overview page was a bit limited.\nYou could <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/free-pro-team@latest/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-profile/pinning-items-to-your-profile\">select what repositories you wanted to pin</a>\nor choose to <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/free-pro-team@latest/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-profile/showing-an-overview-of-your-activity-on-your-profile\">display your activity overview</a>\nbelow your yearly contributions. However, these options didn’t really allow you to express yourself.</p>\n<p>With the introduction of the <strong>GitHub profile README</strong>, you’re able to add some personality to your profile\nwith the full power of <a href=\"https://www.markdownguide.org/\">Markdown</a>.\nThe new feature is a bit of an Easter egg. It doesn’t seem to have ever been officially announced,\nthough it’s <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/free-pro-team@latest/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-profile/managing-your-profile-readme\">fully documented</a>.\nIt appears to have been released in early July 2020.</p>\n<p>If you’d like to set this up for your own profile simply:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/new\">Create a repo</a> with the same name as your username</li>\n<li>Create a <strong>README.md</strong> file in that repo’s root</li>\n<li>Put some content in it!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The README will then render at the top of your profile page.\nFor more information, see the GitHub documentation on <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/free-pro-team@latest/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-profile/managing-your-profile-readme\">Managing your profile README</a>.</p>\n<p>This is my GitHub profile README at the time of writing (layout may differ):</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api?username=scottg489&#x26;show_icons=true&#x26;count_private=true&#x26;line_height=34\" alt=\"GitHub Stats\">\n<img src=\"https://github-readme-stats.vercel.app/api/top-langs/?username=scottg489&#x26;cache_seconds=1800&#x26;hide=python\" alt=\"Top Languages\"></p>\n<p> Check out <a href=\"https://github.com/ScottG489\">my GitHub profile page</a> to view the current version.</p>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{"id":"personalize-your-github-profile-page","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Personalize your GitHub profile page"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#personalize-your-github-profile-page","ariaLabel":"personalize your github profile page permalink","className":["anchor","after"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22